ter threat of legal action as a result of a significant widening of their statutory responsibilities under the companies bill, lawyers and opposition politicians warned yesterday, write Bob Sherwood and Jean Eaglesham.\par \par \uc2 The bill codifies directors' duties for the first time. The government has said it is not intended to add to the board's legal burden but the scope and vague definition of duties in the new law has triggered concerns it could become a platform for disgruntled shareholders to pursue directors into court.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Directors have a duty under existing company law only to take their shareholders' best interests into account. But the bill says directors should also consider how their decisions could affect employees, suppliers, customers and even the community and the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Neil Fagan, head of the corporate and financial services litigation group at Lovells, the law firm, said: "We are getting \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  issues coming into the concept of what directors must now have regard to. Directors are going to have to take broader advice on a wider range of issues."\par \par \uc2 The Conservatives said the bill could have the unintended consequence of imposing extra burdens on boards rather than simplifying the reams of decades-old corporate law. David Willetts, the shadow trade and industry spokesman, said: "We all understand the need for a tidying-up bill. However, the problem is that in the process of tidying up, they seem to have smuggled in some quite significant changes.\par \par \uc2 "They seem to be imposing further obligations on directors of business in a way that's very hard to pin down and could lead to endless legal challenges."\par \par \uc2 Lawyers said it would take a long time before it became clear - through a code of practice or case law - exactly what the new requirements for directors meant in practice.\par \par \uc2 The prospect of "derivative actions" - lawsuits against individual directors brought by shareholders rather than the company - would also be a concern, Mr Fagan said.\par \par \uc2 The impact of the measure in the bill allowing investors to bring such lawsuits will depend in part on how courts use their power to veto such actions, lawyers said.\par \par \uc2 Matthew Newick, a partner at Clifford Chance, the law firm, said he could "not see the bill leading to a flood of investor claims". \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 20051104L103.325\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 ccat : \uc2