Mr Brendan Barber.\par \par \uc2 Sir, Gordon Brown's announcement that the government is to abolish the newly introduced operating and financial review is a slap in the face for those trying to ensure that business is more accountable for its wider impacts on society and the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  ("Brown to scrap reporting rule", November 28).\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The OFR emerged from a multi-stakeholder consultation process that began in 1998 under the auspices of the government's company law review, amid calls for mandatory social and environmental reporting from non-governmental organisations, trade unions, forward-looking businesses and large parts of the investment community.\par \par \uc2 It is the responsibility of government to weigh up the costs and benefits of proposed regulation for all sectors of society. This consideration must include the impact on companies' wider stakeholders such as employees, communities and the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Investors and consumers have indicated their support for the kind of disclosure the OFR would bring. In February this year, the Investment Management Association "welcomed the government seeking to improve the transparency and accountability of companies by making the OFR mandatory for quoted companies". While an overwhelming 94 per cent of those interviewed in a recent MORI poll on business behaviour thought that companies should report on their effects on society and the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 Clearly a lot of water has passed under the bridge since June, when Elliot Morley, minister of state for climate change and \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 , stated that "the OFR will succeed in, amongst other things, substantially increasing the quality of environmental reporting by quoted companies".\par \par \uc2 When the UK government welcomes delegates to its European Union presidency \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  conference this week, it will have much explaining to do.\par \par \uc2 Deborah Doane,\par \par \uc2 Director,\par \par \uc2 CORE Coalition (The Corporate Responsibility Coalition),\par \par \uc2 London EC2A 3EA\par \par \uc2 Brendan Barber,\par \par \uc2 General Secretary,\par \par \uc2 Trades Union Congress,\par \par \uc2 London WC1B 3LS \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 20051201L122.055\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 i831 : \uc2 Financial Investments | iinv : \uc2 Investing/Securities\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\asp