rthy-Fry MP and Baroness Thornton.\par \par \uc2 Sir, The government's company legislation proposals in relation to directors' duties and reporting ("A happy ending to a sorry legislative story", May 5 and "Companies win greater litigation protection", May 4) are disappointing to parliamentarians, the public and progressive companies alike.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 While the restoration of the requirement to report on social and environmental issues is a relief all round, the absence of clear reporting standards will severely undermine the comparability of the reports. No one would suggest that companies be left to determine their own financial accounting standards. The failure to establish clear standards for environmental and social reporting risks reducing the competitiveness of forward-looking companies and further exposing employees, affected communities and the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  to reckless acts of corporate abuse.\par \par \uc2 The Company Law Reform Bill provides an opportunity to redefine the terms of reference of the company for the first time in 150 years. The trade justice movement and corporate responsibility coalition (Core) are urging parliamentarians to support amendments that will help create a balance between companies' rights and responsibilities, in line with one of the long-standing commitments of the co-operative movement.\par \par \uc2 More than 100,000 members of the public have already written to their MP calling for changes that would oblige directors to take responsibility for their companies' environmental and social impacts, report on these impacts and for all affected communities to have fair rights of redress.\par \par \uc2 Amendments to enhance directors' duties are being debated in the House of Lords this week. A recent ICM poll found that nine out of 10 UK voters want enforceable standards for \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  demonstrating that they are clearly in favour of new rules.\par \par \uc2 Sarah McCarthy-Fry,\par \par \uc2 Labour/Co-operative, Portsmouth North\par \par \uc2 Baroness Thornton,\par \par \uc2 Member of the House of Lords, Labour/Co-operative \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 20060510L116.035\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 gpol : \uc2 Domestic Politics | nlte : \uc2 Letter to the Editor | c13 : \uc2 Regulation/Government Policy | gcat : \uc2 Political/General News | gpir : \uc2 Politics/International Relations | ncat : \uc2 Content Types | nfact : \uc2 Factiva Filters | nfce : \uc2 FC&E Exclusion Filter | nfcpin : \uc2 FC&E Industry N