clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 (Copyright (c) 2006, Dow Jones & Company, Inc.) \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 More large companies are aligning disclosures related to their social-responsibility practices with a set of international guidelines, according to a recent study.\par \par \uc2 Many companies issue documents called corporate-sustainability or \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social\b0 \highlight\uc2 -\b \highlight22\uc2 responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  reports in which they disclose information about their environmental stewardship, labor practices, community involvement and other issues. But the information contained in those reports can vary.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Now, more Standard &Poor's 100 companies are adopting guidelines set by the Global Reporting Initiative for these reports, according to the study released in June by the Social Investment Research Analyst Network. The GRI guidelines specify what type of information should go into \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social\b0 \highlight\uc2 -\b \highlight22\uc2 responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  reports.\par \par \uc2 The increase in disclosures that use the GRI guidelines follows greater numbers of investors asking companies to use these measurements, according to Steve Lippman, one author of the study.\par \par \uc2 In proxies filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission, shareholder proposals requesting that companies use the Global Reporting Initiative guidelines have appeared for seven companies so far this year compared with none in 2005.\par \par \uc2 Some companies have opposed those calls, saying their disclosures and practices concerning the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 , labor and other related issues already cover shareholders' concerns. Among the companies whose directors have opposed proposals asking for GRI reports are Safeway Inc., Dean Foods Co., Kroger Co., Wendy's International Inc. and General Dynamics Corp.\par \par \uc2 According to the study by the Social Investment Research Analyst Network, 37 of the Standard &Poor's 100 companies currently use GRI guidelines in their reports to investors and the public. The study focused on reports available on these large companies' Web sites, among other methods of distribution.\par \par \uc2 The reports usually are dozens of pages long, providing descriptions of a company's practices in categories that the Global Reporting Initiative benchmarks cover.\par \par \uc2 "Increasingly, companies are looking to the GRI [guidelines]," Mr. Lippman said. Industry leaders reason that it makes sense to have one standard to measure efforts in certain areas, and as more companies use the guidelines, others are following suit, he said. "There's a little bit of a case of 'follow the leader' here. Companies don't want to be really out front or really behind."\par \par \uc2 The research study covered reports issued between June 2005 and May 2006. A similar review issued in June 2005 for the prior 12 months found 25 of the S&P 100 companies issued \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social\b0 \highlight\uc2 -\b \highlight22\uc2 responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  reports incorporating the GRI guidelines. Four of the 37 companies were new to the S&P 100 Index in the most recent period and weren't included in the previous year's count.\par \par \uc2 Weyerhaeuser Co. has been using the GRI guidelines since 2002, Emily Collings, of the company's \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 , health and safety department, said.\par \par \uc2 "There's no regulatory driver" for \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social\b0 \highlight\uc2 -\b \highlight22\uc2 responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  reporting, Ms. Collings said. "The GRI is the closest thing for standards for this type of reporting. It gives us some credibility for how we release that information."\par \par \uc2 H.J. Heinz Co. produced its first corporate-responsibility report in June and chose to use GRI guidelines, according to an SEC filing. Heinz spokesman Mike Yeomans said the company plans to continue to use the guidelines.\par \par \uc2 The Global Reporting Initiative is an international organization of companies, government agencies and nonprofit groups. Its reporting guidelines, first issued in 2000 and revised in 2002, ask companies to describe their business generally, such as management structure and operations. It also asks companies to look at specifics such as energy usage and impact on local natural habitats where the businesses operate. Companies are further asked to examine their community impact, such as effect on the local economy and labor issues, such as employee turnover, union representation and worker safety and training.\par \par \uc2 Wal-Mart Stores Inc., which has faced waves of criticism about its labor practices and effect on local economies and the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 , has said it plans to issue its first corporate-sustainability report next year. Shareholders have asked the company to use the GRI guidelines. Wal-Mart, in an SEC filing, indicated it may use the guidelines, but said it doesn't believe that following a single set of measurements will benefit the company or its shareholders.\par \par \uc2 GRI plans to issue a new version of its guidelines in October, according to the organization's Web site.\par \par \uc2 The guidelines aren't used only to satisfy shareholders' demands for disclosure, Mr. Lippman said. GRI guidance also allows reporting of other measures that could benefit a company in less quantifiable ways, such as employee training and job satisfaction.\par \par \uc2 "The process of reporting tends to lead naturally to better performance," Mr. Lippman said. If a company is examining its energy usage, for example, it will want to find ways to cut energy costs. If a firm studies its recycling efforts, it may want to show investors and the public an improvement in that area the next year.\par \par \uc2 "There's kind of a natural inclination to want to report better numbers next year," Mr. Lippman said. "What gets measured, gets managed." \par \par {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.djreprints.com/link/DJRFactiva.html?FACTIVA=wjco20060906000019"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 License this article from Dow Jones Reprint Service}}}\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \