ic International. "They have had to make major decisions, manage a number of people and teams, have restructured, and have been restructured. At other schools, many of the students have been very good analysts but have not led large projects."\par \par \uc2 In this year's survey, IMD received its top scores from recruiters for students' international knowledge, work experience and ability to perform well in teams. The lowest ratings were for commitment to \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  and value for the money invested in the recruiting effort.\par \par \uc2 Situated in a stunning lakeside area surrounded by mountains, IMD offers an intensive 11-month program that aims to satisfy multinational companies' need for leaders, not just managers. Students learn about the perspectives of a company's many stakeholders, including governments, nongovernmental organizations, the financial community and the media. They also participate in a "discovery expedition" to a country facing a difficult business \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  -- Argentina this year -- and they work in teams on international consulting projects for big companies.\par \par \uc2 Some recruiters complain about IMD's small pool of graduates, but not Mr. Krasnodebski. "If you are looking to hire a number of M.B.A.s, it could be an issue," he says. "However, if you are looking for targeted people to fill specific, challenging and mature roles, it is not."\par \par \uc2 IMD ON IMD\par \par \uc2 (Data provided by IMD)\par \par \uc2 M.B.A. enrollment: 153\par \par \uc2 Full-time: 90\par \par \uc2 Executive: 63\par \par \uc2 Annual tuition: $44,980\par \par \uc2 Annual room and board: $18,810\par \par \uc2 PROFILE OF FULL-TIME STUDENTS\par \par \uc2 GMAT score: 680 (mean)\par \par \uc2 680 (median)\par \par \uc2 Years of full-time work experience: 7 (mean)\par \par \uc2 7 (median)\par \par \uc2 Demographics\par \par \uc2 Male: 82%\par \par \uc2 Female: 18%