mon Zapata, a survey respondent and head of business planning and analysis for Novartis Pharma Mexico. "Their M.B.A. gives them enough knowledge to live by our code of conduct and corporate citizenship guidelines without any major explanations."\par \par \uc2 IPADE views management as "a people affair" and therefore emphasizes the personal and ethical implications of any business decision. In addition to traditional areas like marketing, operations and finance, IPADE's academic departments include the political and social \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  of organizations, philosophy and business, business and family, and human behavior.\par \par \uc2 Established in 1967 in Mexico City by a group of businessmen who wanted to make management of local companies more professional, IPADE offers both a two-year M.B.A. program for recent college graduates and a two-year executive M.B.A. for more seasoned managers. It teaches general-management skills through the analysis of business cases.\par \par \uc2 In the survey, recruiters gave IPADE very high marks for students' work ethic, personal ethics and integrity, and teamwork skills. It received its lowest scores for students' previous work experience and international knowledge.\par \par \uc2 Mr. Zapata says IPADE should require at least three years of full-time work experience for admission to the M.B.A. program instead of accepting some applicants soon after college. IPADE also "needs to further develop international contact" for its students, he says, "to strengthen their ability to work in multicultural teams and read different cultures in a more natural manner." Unlike other schools in the International ranking, IPADE isn't very diverse, attracting 90% of its students from Mexico.\par \par \uc2 IPADE ON IPADE\par \par \uc2 (Data provided by IPADE)\par \par \uc2 M.B.A. enrollment: 562\par \par \uc2 Full-time: 152\par \par \uc2 Executive: 410\par \par \uc2 Annual tuition: $16,261\par \par \uc2 Annual room and board: $10,500\par \par \uc2 PROFILE OF FULL-TIME STUDENTS\par \par \uc2 GMAT score: 615 (mean)\par \par \uc2 610 (median)\par \par \uc2 Years of full-time work experience: 3 (mean)\par \par \uc2 3.5 (median)\par \par \uc2 Demographics\par \par \uc2 Male: 82%\par \par \uc2 Female: 18%\par \par \uc2 Mexican citizens/residents: 90%\par \par \uc2 Foreign nationals: 10%\par \par \uc2 CLASS OF 2005 EMPLOYMENT DATA\par \par \uc2 Percentage of job-seeking full-time graduates who:\par \par \uc2 Received offers prior to or within three months of graduation: 96%\par \par \uc2 Accepted offers prior to or within three months of graduation: 91%\par \par \uc2 Average compensation of full-time graduates who accepted employment\par \par \uc2 Annual base salary: $38,022\par \par \uc2 Signing bonus: N.A.\par \par \uc2 Other guaranteed compensation: $11,194\par \par \uc2 Companies hiring the most 2005 full-time graduates:\par \par \uc2 HSBC: 6\par \par \uc2 Banamex, Farmacos Nacionales: 3 each\par \par \uc2 Three of the most famous graduates of M.B.A. program:\par \par \uc2 Sergio Alejandro Garcia de Alba Zepeda, class of 1980, Mexico's Minister of Economy\par \par \uc2 Marcos A. Martinez Gavica, class of 1978, president, Mexican Banks Association\par \par \uc2 Santiago Garcia Garcia, class of 1978, general director, Comercial Mexicana Group\par \par \uc2 THE RECRUITERS SPEAK\par \par \uc2 IPADE's most impressive features:\par \par \uc2 "Emphasis on ethics and values"\par \par \uc2 "Teamwork and hard-working style"\par \par \uc2 "Leadership and strategic thinking"\par \par \uc2 IPADE's major shortcomings:\par \par \uc2 "Students' lack of professional work experience"\par \par \uc2 "M.B.A.s need more international exposure"\par \par \uc2 "Some professors not up-to-date in new business thinking"\par \par \uc2 4) London Business School\par \par \uc2 Cited for its impressive multicultural \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  and finance curriculum, London Business School placed fourth in The Wall Street Journal/Harris Interactive's International ranking.\par \par \uc2 In the survey, recruiters gave the school its best marks for students' analytical and problem-solving skills, strategic thinking, and international knowledge and experience. It received its lowest scores for the career-services office, experiential learning in the curriculum, and commitment to \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \par \uc2 "LBS does a good job at creating networking opportunities between companies and students," says Nelson Allen, a survey respondent and marketing director for Samsung Electronics Europe. The school contacted his company about participating in an industry forum on internal consulting, which enabled Samsung to build student interest in its own internal consulting program and make some potential recruiting contacts.\par \par \uc2 London Business School encourages student interaction with the business world in other ways, too. In the M.B.A. program's second-year project, student teams consult for clients ranging from multinationals and start-ups to charities. As part of its leadership focus, the school also assigns students to a "shadowing project" in which they observe a manager on the job for up to five days.\par \par \uc2 Students can choose academic concentrations in finance, marketing, entrepreneurial management, technology management, strategy, change management, private equity or international business. About two-thirds of recent graduates have taken jobs in financial services and management consulting.\par \par \uc2 The school gives students flexibility in how fast they complete their M.B.A. degree. The standard program is 21 months, but some students can finish in as little as 15 months through course waivers for competence in economics or accounting.\par \par \uc2 The school heavily promotes its international culture to recruiters and prospective students. About 90% of students are from 