 video for FT.com\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 This week, Sir Martin Sorrell, chief executive of WPP\par \par \uc2 Financial Times: There has been a lot of turbulence in emerging markets this week, particularly in China where I i know you're very active\par \par \uc2 Sir Martin Sorrell:China is very important to us. It's our fourth largest business... will be our third largest business in Beijing, 2008. But I think it's understandable - what goes up can't go up forever. But we rather like this softness, or perhaps suggestion of softness or change because it will be a bigger buying opportunity for us as everybody flees the markets. But we've seen other things in emerging markets: we've seen problems in Hungary we've seen a coup in Thailand, we've seen some corruption issues in Brazil. There's bound to be bumpiness in emerging markets because it's high-risk high reward, but we really like those markets and are determined to increase our market position in those markets.\par \par \uc2 FT: Another really eye catching event as been the Clington Global Initiative, particualry Richard Branson's rather flamboyant pledge\par \par \uc2 Sir Martin: Fantastic publicity for Richard Branson...yes....well, I think it's emblematic of this trend and shift that we're seeing in business.. business understanding corporate responsibility, \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 , getting involved . And the global warming issue is an issue that's been embraced by Buffett and by Gates, and James Murdoch has also taken a big initiative... we've seen the Gore film. So, we're going to see a lot more involvement in the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  - Tom Friedman is doing I think a book and a TV series on this whole area of global warming. And I think that China, interestingly, will be one of the countries that emerges as the champion globally dealing with the issue and I think Beijing 2008 will be a good example of that.\par \par \uc2 FT: In your own space the media spacee theres been a remarkable development suggesting the way in which the ounger generation has really taken to new technology...\par \par \uc2 Sir Martin: ...a 3- year-old kid buying a car on the internet, on eBay for $8-$9000 without his parents knowledge- well this is a change in media consumption habits that's having a big impact on traditional media... so, if you think it's been difficult up to now just wait for the next generation. But at the same time we're seeing ITV under pressure in the UK - predictions that fourth quarter revenues will be down by 21 per cent - that's a big number - but when there's a unanimity of view that something's going south, it's usually the point at which - the tipping point - when it goes north. So, whoever takes over ITV, I think, will have an interesting opportunity\par \par \uc2 FT: and I know you've been following the Ryder Cup ...I wonder what you think are the wider implications of what's happened there\par \par \uc2 Sir Martin: Well...a tremendous sporting occasion, all kudos to Darren Clarke, particularly after his wife died of cancer -a month later to come back in this way... but I think the really interesting point about the Ryder Cup...it was the triumph of the team over the individuals and I think that's a lesson for all of us\par \par \uc2 And now the prediction-\par \par \uc2 Sir Martin: now my prediction-with some trepidation-the papers have been full about Blair and Brown I will predict that the next election will be won by Cameron. And the next US election, by Mrs Clinton-.God help me-.\par \par \uc2 That was Sir Martin Sorrell, CEO of WPP.\par \par \uc2 Next week, Robert Rubin, of Citigroup \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 51726156\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CO\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 wirp : \uc2 WPP PLC\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 i838 : \uc2 Advertising | iadv : \uc2 Advertising/Public Relations/Marketing | imark : \uc2 Marketing\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\