par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 David Cameron's anti-business rhetoric is designed merely to change the Tories' image as "rapacious capitalist pigs", and does not herald a raft of tough new regulation, the shadow trade and industry secretary said.\par \par \uc2 "Nothing we say is against business, it's designed to correct a political misconception," Alan Duncan said in an interview with the FT. He said a Conservative government would rely mainly on exhortation to improve corporate behaviour, "because we want to deregulate ... ?Business should have to adhere to a few simple decencies, not an encyclopaedia of directions."\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Mr Cameron's criticisms of "irresponsible" business, including attacks on named companies such as Bhs and WH?Smith, have made "some business people a bit huff", Mr Duncan acknowledged. But he said the Tories were reassuring executives that the leader's comments were part of a rebranding, rather than an ideological, exercise.\par \par \uc2 Mr Duncan signalled that the party would also abandon its election proposal to dismantle the Department of Trade and Industry by scrapping 80 per cent of its budget. "I have inherited no such commitment ... ?we [will] keep the DTI," Mr Duncan said.\par \par \uc2 Mr Duncan admitted that the pre-election pledge to eviscerate the DTI had alarmed business, which feared it would lose its voice in government. "The golden goose needs a guardian. And I am that guardian," he said. The Conservatives will now review the DTI's structure and remit to convert it into a "proper industrial, commercial, trade, energy department", he said.\par \par \uc2 The Tory leader's message on the need for business to face up to its responsibilities on such issues as the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  and work-life balance is not a prelude to much tougher regulation, Mr Duncan suggested. "\b \highlight22\uc2 Corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  is largely a cultural thing." \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 51800032\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 ncat : \uc2 Content Types | nfact : \uc2 Factiva Filters | nedc : \uc2 Comment