idctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 J Sainsbury said Justin King was on track to receive his Pounds 5m bonus pay-out after the chief executive beat his own sales targets and said the supermarket chain's momentum was strong. \par \par \uc2 Philip Hampton, chairman, said that if Mr King, who is midway through his three-year recovery programme, sustained this performance over the next 18 months, "the incentive scheme would pay to the upper end or the maximum of the scale". \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Mr King said he had hit Pounds 1.3bn of his Pounds 2.5bn sales growth target, while earnings per share - which need to double to about 20p for the full pay-out - reached 7.5p at the half-year stage. \par \par \uc2 The ebullient chief executive said consumers' desire for "fresh, quality and healthy food" was playing into Sainsbury's hands. Sales rose 8 per cent to Pounds 9.7bn. \par \par \uc2 "We are ahead of the industry in responding to consumers," said Mr King. He said he was beating Tesco "without a doubt" on \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  and \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  issues. \par \par \uc2 His bullish comments round off a good run for the company, which in October announced a 6.6 per cent rise in underlying sales, matching arch-rival Tesco's growth. However, some analysts expressed disappointment at Sainsbury's operating margin. David McCarthy, retail analyst with Citigroup, wrote in a note that the operating margin, coming in at 2.43 per cent, was below expectations of 2.65 per cent. "The company may be pleased with this result but Wm Morrison's margin is now at 2.7 per cent having started from a lower level." \par \par \uc2 Mr King said he would work harder on the bottom line in the coming year. Underlying profits before tax came in at Pounds 254m last year, having been more than Pounds 600m in the three previous years. It is expected to make about Pounds 360m in profits this year. \par \par \uc2 "It is a pretty dramatic recovery of sales, and we can not only grow our top line, we can grow our profits too," said Mr King. Sainsbury enjoyed a 7 per cent rise in market share in the three months to November 5, against last year, according to TNS data. The company said transactions had grown by 1.5m over the half. \par \par \uc2 It also said it spent about Pounds 200m during the period refurbishing or extending stores as it looked to add 2.5 per cent to 3 per cent more space to its portfolio over the year. Profit before tax more than doubled to Pounds 194m, affected by a one-off expense in the prior period. Earnings per share more than doubled to 7.5p. Underlying operating profits rose 32 per cent to Pounds 215m. \par \par \uc2 The shares closed 1 per cent lower at 408.25p  \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RF\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 20061116L121.143\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\ro